widgets_values:
Upscale to whatever size you want, take into account that the image may be already upscaled if you used a upscale model previuosly, you may even want to downscale here to a desired resolution or a negative "scale_by".

Don't touch the upscale method or the mask will be lost and the workflow will fail.

You may change the tiles size or overlap, but these settings work fine.

You can check the resulting tiles with their masked area in the "ImageAndMaskPreview" node. The masked areas are red. If you want to upscale the whole image, everything should be red.

You will have to download a model the first time if you didn't have already, you might experiment with different florence2 finetunes and settings in the "florence2Run" node.

Use flash attention 2 if you have it installed, if not change it to sdpa.

Here the controlnet and models are loadad. Also sage attention is selected if installed.

I highly recommend the nunchaku quantized models, if you want to use fp16/8 or gguf feel free to change the loaders, it should work the same (way slower though).

You might even proced without controlnet if you use a low denoise later.

Here the samplig settings.  You may want to play with the ControlNet values and the denoise value, what I left as default is what usually works better.

Bypass the "ApplyControlnet" node if you want to proced without controlnet, it will be slightly faster and use less memory, but you might see artifacts or wierd things if the denoise is too high. Still, as the tiles are captioned, even without controlnet this workflow is less prone to hallucinations than older tile methods.
Only activate this group if you whish to downscale the upscaled area back into the original sized image. Kind of an Adetailer for high resolutions/low memory.

You can upscale the whole image or only an area (optionally bringing it back to the original resolution for an "adetailer" effect). 

IMPORTANT: If you want to just upscale the whole image, you must mask the whole image in the mask editor. Use the bucket tool.

Choose here the upscale models, you might want to do a x4 model, or only a cleanup with a dejpeg or denoise model. Bypass the "Upscale Image (using Model)" nodes as needed.

Whatever you do, you must match whatever upscale do the models in the green "Match the upscale model !!!" node. Don't touch the upscale method.
